  "texts": [
    "The net encoding rate is r ≈ 1/(2d 2), which quickly becomes impractical as one is forced to choose a large code distance, due to, for instance, the physical errors being close to the threshold value.",
    "By contrast, BB codes have encoding rate r ≫ 1/d 2, see Table 1 for code examples.",
    "To the best of our knowledge, all codes shown in Table 1 are new.",
    "The distance-12 code [[144, 12, 12]] may be the most promising for near-term demonstrations, as it combines large distance and high net encoding rate r = 1/24.",
    "For comparison, the distance-11 surface code has a net encoding rate r = 1/241."
  ],
